# node_thumbnail_face.scn — 活體牙 (EXPERIENCE_SCOPE_GAPS #13): a node whose FIRST output is a
# Texture2D draws a thumbnail of its rendered output on its body, TiXL parity (= external/tixl
# Editor/Gui/MagGraph/Ui/MagGraphCanvas.DrawNode.cs TryDrawTexturePreview: "if firstOutput is
# Slot<Texture2D> ... drawList.AddImage(texture, ...)" — the live cooked texture, drawn scaled on
# the operator body). Our face (node_faces.cpp drawTexturePreviewFace) reads the resident node's
# cooked texture (residentNodeTexture(path) -> PointGraph::residentTexFor, the per-path ensureTex
# the cook fills) and draws it with the same type-colored border. The face records a `thumb:<id>`
# rect via the ONE eye hook so the harness can assert it (alongside the screenshot eye gate).
#
# Cook reality (named fork from TiXL): TiXL evaluates every visible op, so every image op shows a
# thumbnail. Our cook realizes ONE target subtree per frame (the viewed/selected node's chain), so
# a thumbnail appears for a Texture2D node when it is on the cooked chain (here: SELECTED, since the
# viewport follows the selection). This is the honest live state — the texture shown IS the texture
# the node really cooked this frame, never a stale/fake preview.
#
# Asserts (RED -> GREEN):
#   1. A non-image node (id 5, a Points op) NEVER has a thumb — its first output is not Texture2D.
#   2. Clicking the perlin asset creates a LoadImage (id 7, Texture2D out) in Root.
#   3. Selecting that LoadImage cooks its texture -> a `thumb:7` rect appears on its body, AND the
#      clean screenshot shows the perlin texture as a mini-image on the node (capture for the eye).
#   4. The non-image node STILL has no thumb after all this (the gate is the output TYPE, not state).
#
# RED proof: in node_faces.cpp drawTexturePreviewFace, drop the `firstOut->dataType != "Texture2D"`
# gate (so every node tries a thumb) -> step 1/4 FAIL (a Points node would get a thumb:5). Or remove
# the `if (!tex) return false` -> step 3's thumb never appears for a Texture2D node off the chain.

open app/testdata/compound_smoke.swproj
wait 0.3

# --- 1. baseline: a non-image Points node (id 5) has NO thumbnail ---
assert_map '([.items[]? | select(.label == "thumb:5")] | length) == 0'
echo non-image-node-5-has-no-thumb

# --- 2. click the perlin asset -> a LoadImage (Texture2D out) is created in Root as id 7 ---
assert_map_has asset:Lib:images/basic/perlin-noise-rgb.png
do click @asset:Lib:images/basic/perlin-noise-rgb.png
wait 0.5
assert_state '[.lib.symbols[] | select(.id == "Root") | .children[] | select(.symbolId == "sw-type:LoadImage")] | length >= 1'
echo perlin-loadimage-created

# --- 3. select the LoadImage so the viewport cooks it -> its body shows the cooked perlin thumb ---
do selectnode 7
wait 0.6
assert_map_has thumb:7
echo image-node-7-shows-thumb
capture full node_thumbnail
echo screenshot-captured

# --- 4. the non-image node STILL has no thumb (gate is the output TYPE, not cook state) ---
assert_map '([.items[]? | select(.label == "thumb:5")] | length) == 0'
echo non-image-node-5-still-no-thumb
